# IDEAL Metadata Schema

## 1. Title and Publication Details

### Title
✅ **Required**  
📚 [DDI 2.5](https://ddialliance.org/Specification/DDI-Codebook/2.5/XMLSchema/) | [ClinicalTrials.gov](https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/manage-recs/resources)

**Definition:** *The full title of the paper.*  
✏️ **Open text response**

<details>
<summary><strong>Notes for Pilot</strong></summary>

- Can be automatically pulled into SurveyCTO.
- Include subtitle in coding instructions.
- Extracted from citation.
- Tag if experiment was reported elsewhere.

</details>

### Citation
✅ **Required**  
📚 [DDI 2.5](https://ddialliance.org/Specification/DDI-Codebook/2.5/XMLSchema/)

**Definition:** *Complete bibliographic reference.*  
✏️ **Open text response**

### DOI/URL
⚠️ **Optional**  
📚 [DDI 2.5](https://ddialliance.org/Specification/DDI-Codebook/2.5/XMLSchema/)

**Definition:** *DOI or URL to access the paper.*  
✏️ **Open text response**

## 2. Resources

### Type of resource
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### URL of resource
✏️ **Open text response**

### Registration ID
✏️ **Open text response**

### Registry URL
✏️ **Open text response**

### Review board name
✏️ **Open text response**

### Review number
✏️ **Open text response**

## 3. Partners and Funders

### Name of agency involved
✏️ **Open text response**

### Role of agencies
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Type of agency
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

## 4. Topics and Objectives

### Topic of study
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Keywords
✏️ **Open text response**

## 5. Sampling

### Country
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Sub-national location
✏️ **Open text response**

### Unit of randomization
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary and Open text**

### Unit of analysis
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary and Open text**

### Eligibility of experimental population
✏️ **Open text response**

### Recruitment of experimental sample
✏️ **Open text response**

### Sampling from recruited
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Deviation from sample inclusion
✏️ **Open text response**

### Baseline average female share
🔢 **Numeric**

### Baseline average age
🔢 **Numeric**

## 6. Intervention

### Name of intervention
✏️ **Open text response**

### Details of intervention
✏️ **Open text response**

### Name of arm
✏️ **Open text response**

### Number of randomization units per arm
🔢 **Numeric**

### Mapping of intervention to arms
✏️ **Structured Format**

### Intervention assignment strategy
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Timeline of intervention
📅 **Start and End Date**

## 7. Outcome

### Name of the outcome measure
✏️ **Open text response**

### Outcome measure category
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Outcome measurement tool
✏️ **Open text response**

### Outcome measure statistical type
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Outcome measure standardized
🔒 **Yes/No/Don't Know**

### Standardization description
✏️ **Open text response**

### Outcome measure coding
🔒 **Yes/No/Ambiguous/Don't Know**

### Outcome data source
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Outcome measure collection start date
📅 **Date**

### Outcome measure collection end date
📅 **Date**

### Outcome mean
🔢 **Numeric**

### Outcome SD
🔢 **Numeric**

### Outcome sample size
🔢 **Numeric**

### Additional information for clustered RCTs
✏️ **Open text/Numeric**

## 8. Estimates

### Estimation parameter
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Estimand
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Null hypothesis
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Statistical test of hypothesis
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Contrast for the treatment effect
✏️ **Open text response**

### Estimate of the treatment effect
🔢 **Numeric**

### Unit of measure of the treatment effect
✏️ **Open text response**

### Precision
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Precision value
🔢 **Numeric**

### Subgroup of heterogeneous analysis
🔒 **Controlled Vocabulary**

### Description of heterogeneous analysis
✏️ **Open text response**

### Estimates of heterogeneous treatment effects
✏️ **Structured Response**

